UNITED STATES of America ex rel. Louis DE BRITO, Appellant, v. Edward CORSI, as Commissioner of Immigration, Ellis Island, New York, Appellee. No. 488. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. July 9, 1934. William J. Cogan, of New York City, for appellant. Martin Conboy, U. S. Atty., of New York City (Ralph E. Stone, Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Order affirmed on authority of U. S. ex rel. Powlowee v. Day (C. C. A.) 33 F.(2d) 267.
